OL,3,C'Masking is exhausting': MP calls for
OL,4,Cbetter support for neurodivergent
OL,5,Cworkers
OL,7,FClosing the debate, the MP added:
OL,8,F"Neurodivergent people should not have
OL,9,Fto work harder than everyone else just
OL,10,Fto stay afloat...We should be
OL,11,Fdesigning work that works for people,
OL,12,Fnot expecting people to endlessly
OL,13,Fadapt to systems that were never
OL,14,Fdesigned with them in mind.
OL,16,F"If we want our workplaces, and our
OL,17,FParliament, to reflect the society as
OL,18,Fa whole, then neurodivergent people
OL,19,Fmust be able to see a future for
OL,20,Fthemselves."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/10
